   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=615.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Also</span><hr size=1> Ssslippy, what is the duration of your instance?  If you want to get mathematical, let's say it's 0.1 seconds.  That means that in one second, 40 pets could be &quot;hitting&quot; the same mob.  Now decrease that number.  Make it 0.001 seconds.  That means that 4000 pets could be &quot;hitting&quot; the same mob.<br>
<br>
If you go even further and say that the instance is infinitly small, that means that an infinite number of pets can hit the mobs.<br>
<br>
So that proves that any number of pets can hit the mob at any given time.<br>
<br>
That being said, I don't think Verant really cares about calculating &quot;instances&quot; like that.  They would be crazy to do so.  So ditch the whole &quot;4 pets hitting in an instance&quot; theory.  Any number of summoned pets can attack a mob. <p>--------------------------<BR>
