<br>
Eastern Karana has this code (much to my surprise), my bard (albiet a few lvl's ago) would load selo's up and grab every blue hound, lion, crag he could find.  Now he had to be careful to not get hit mind you.  The best example I can say without a doubt (and also the best way to kite them all), is to use 1 particular type so that their run speed will make them group together (whereass, 6 crags run alot slower than 6 hounds wich run slower than 6 lions, which makes a harder kite and a bad example).<br>
<br>
So one pull I actually got 14 hounds (and stalkers but they run the same speed) to give chase to me.  To get them in range for my AoE song to hit them I actually had to be real close (which always resulted in inside) to melee range.  With the way it was coded it was timeable to have all the mobs inside AoE range when the AoE actually hit, but I could ONLY be hit by 3 of the mobs at a time.  This resulted in 2 things happening first some of the mobs would politely wait their turn (right out of melee range) others would bolt (which kinda looked like an exploding star).  So it was selo, AoE, selo to avoid losing the train I worked soo hard to build up (believe me they could barely touch me when they were evens so I could have stood there in one place singing).<br>
<br>
That being said, once in a blue moon a 4th 5th 6th and so on would sometimes stand in melee range attacking in between others attacks.  Does that mean that it's coded for 6 to be able to be beating me at once? NO but it does mean they can/will stand there waiting for their turn.<br>
<br>
Also by the time I left there I didn't have any shooting away from me once I got my 3 on me.  I noticed when I packed them right, all the adds would stand there waiting there turn (some attacking here and there but never more than 3 at any time, the rest standing there as if mez'ed).  To create this result they had to be tightly packed (looking as close to 1 mob as they could), and it required absolutely no lag, as long as they were all less than arms length away when the first one was able to attack, then NONE of them shot out away from me and basically I was able to get the xp of 10+ blues while only taking damage from 3, cause 7+ were acting like they were mez'ed while taking dmg from my AoE.  Exploit?  Probably, but if I can get 10+ mobs on me (with only 3 attacking) in a zone where it's coded for a max of 3 mobs at a time, then I see NO reason why one couldn't get a screenshot of 12 pets on a mob at once, you just have to keep in mind that only 4 of them were attacking at ANY given time.<br>
<br>
My friend didn't believe me that only 3 were attacking me once, so I staggered the mobs a bit then went in to melee again and politely dropped 3 onto him.  He believed me at that point, erm right after he finished loading. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uscrubfire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>scrubfire</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 205<br> <font color=#333333>(8/8/02 7:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=615.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: This might give some a clue!!!</span><hr size=1> Yes, but...<br>
